This paper deals with data integration and analysis, which is a common topic in the database (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of machine learning techniques to estimate missing data values and assess the impact of unknown unknowns also suggests a connection to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on aggregate queries and the use of statistical techniques suggests a connection to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
